title: DawnforgedCast - The Ultimate Psionic Mindbender in 5E D&D
description: (5E D&D) Unearthed Arcana - The Mystic Class After a few previous iterations and false starts we finally have Wizard's 5th Edition Dungeons and Dragons version of Psionics in the Mystic class. Within we find that psionics live up to their reputation of being highly powerful and versatile, with complex new mechanics not for the uninitiated. The authors did a great job of providing many options for the class, such as offering six archetypes to choose from, including the popular Soul Knife, as well as dozens of new powers and abilities in the form of Disciplines that really let you customize your character. More options for the classes has been my recommendation for quite a while and it is great to see this philosophy being implemented more and more in Unearthed Arcana. Overall the Mystic is a great take on the Psionic class and one I recommend you playtest soon!

title: Circles Demo a programming challenge
description: After completing chapter 19, going over the CIRCLE command, I thought it would be cool to write a demo to show off all the various ways we can create and modify a circle. So I did that, my demo does the following: Shows circles of expanding sized radius' Show circle ellipses of expanding height Show circle ellipses of expanding width shows partial circle arcs, going clockwise shows partial circle arcs, going clockwise utilizes a subroutine for each section to create a title screen with centered text, random colors, and musical delay utilizes a subroutine for each section to set a random graphical PMODE, sets random foreground and background colors, sets those colors using the COLOR FC,BC command Clears the screen with the PCLS command, and sets a random color mode by activating Screen 1,0 or 1,1 randomly Lastly, it has a subroutine that pauses and returns, and this routine is used whenever animation is used and a section, and it's used to pause between sections. Rather than showing off how I did it right away, I thought it would be great to set this up as a challenge to see who can create something similar. You can email me the code, or a disk image with the program to ogStevieStrow@gmail.com or just put the code as a comment here. Can't wait to see what everyone comes up with! If you'd like to make a donation use this link:

As an original member of the X-Men, Hank’s condition still continues to wildly mutate over time. Despite these challenges, he remains undeterred as the team’s wittiest mutant of many talents. Genius. title: GDC 2017 Flash Forward: Practical Contract Law 201 For Indie Developers: Moderately Scary Edition
description: Don't sign that! ... yet. Join games lawyer Chris Reid in the follow-up to last year's #1 rated Summit talk, as he walks indie developers through the single most common legal issue they will encounter: contracts. IP, privacy, licensing, distribution and almost every legal issue important to developers is handled with a contract. Chris will cover the five contracts every indie needs to understand: contractor agreements, publishing agreements, game development agreements, NDAs and EULAs. For each type of contract, he will describe when it comes up, why it matters, and what terms to include and avoid. Now you can sign. title: #Archery
description: #Archery is the second game made by VRUnicorns. VR Unicorns were the developers behind #SelfieTennis which is a Cartoony Tennis game you play against yourself, and try to wrack up a good run. #Archery is a collection of mini-games tied together by a teleporting tablet. #Archery is in early access and I hope to see it improved and expanded on. Each of the minigames while fun, were quite short, and need more to turn them into full games. I also would like to see some kind of music during the games. I would love to see each of the minigames made into much longer experiences with leaderboards. I will come back and play this again after some updates and hopefully they can keep improving it. I really like the paperboy game the most, and wish it was a full length experience.

title: Broken Flowers: Geralt & Dandellion's Women (Witcher 3 | Vespula, Elihal, Marabella, Molly, Rosa)
description: Geralt had learned from the dreamer Corinne Tilly that Ciri contracted me while in Novigrad. He thus made his way to the Rosemary and Thyme, a charming establishment which I had inherited from an admirer of my poetry, for he, quite rationally, expected to find me there. His search for Cici seemed closer to a happy conclusion than ever before. Alas, fate had raised his hopes only to dash them cruelly back to the ground. Geralt did not find me at my proprietorship. His despair was partially lifted when he came across our old friend, Zoltan Chivay – but the dwarf had just returned from a long journey and knew nothing of my fate or that of Ciri. Concern wrinkling his brown, Zoltan helpled Geralt search every corner of the establishment for clues about where I might be. Other than a few triflings, all they found was a planner containing notes about the women I had met with in the days prior to my disappearance. They divided the names between then and ventured into the city to find the women and ask what they knew. Geralt conversed with the ladies whose company I had recently graced. Though each had fond memories of these encounters, none knew where I might be now. Geralt gleaned from their stories that there was one person who might know more: a famous and talented trobairitz named Priscilla. It so happened this ravishing starlet was still in town and performing every night at the Kingfisher Inn. Like it or not, the witcher was in for an evening of fine culture. at the end of which he hoped to take the artist aside for a serious chat. Priscilla told Geralt about the ruckus I had supposedly raised at Whoreson Junior's headquarters, and that I had been planning to rob treasure from Sigi Reuven, a man better known to Geralt as Sigismund Dijkstra, former head of Redanian intelligence. Geralt now realized I was up the proverbial creek in a leaky boat without a paddle, surrounded by man-eating crocodiles – and he would have to swim to my rescue. "Broken Flowers" quest from "The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt" game. ► Watch more Witcher 3 videos:

title: ARK: Survival Evolved - underwater locations
description: January 17, 2017 - The ceaselessly sleepless team at Studio Wildcard today released a new content update for ARK: Survival Evolved on Xbox One and PlayStation®4 that adds a bevy of new beasts, and two expansive underwater environments to explore. This new update brings the console versions of the massively popular survival game on-par with its PC version through v253, and includes two full-scale underwater caves that are progression oriented with artifacts, while unleashing five new creatures! The PlayStation®4 update also adds the “Procedurally Generated Maps” feature on-par with PC and Xbox One, which allows players to generate an infinite variety of new ARKs to experience. The update is free, and available now on Xbox Live and tomorrow on PlayStation Network. New Dinos and Creatures! Cnidaria Omnimorph: A combination of everything good and bad about various species of Jellyfish, the Cnidaria is too simple to tame or train, but tribes keep schools of them around for their bioluminescence and their ability to sting. Containing them in pools around a camp is a great way to make a barrier of swimming, stinging security that also illuminates the night. They also drop a special biotoxin which can be used to create shocking torpor darts and is 2x as powerful as regular ones. Troodon Magnanimus: Outside of human beings, the Troodon might just be the most clever creature on the islands. You don't "tame" a Troodon, you earn its loyalty through its social nature and love of the hunt. While Troodon is considered a smaller relative of the island's Raptors, they are no less dangerous, especially with their love of hunting at night. Pegomastax Fructarator: Life ain't easy when you're at the bottom of the food chain on carnivore-filled islands, just ask the Pegomastax. This is a relatively harmless herbivore who prefers to live alone and gorges on just about any plants it can find. Far from the definition of "pretty," Pegomastax features a nasty looking beak (with tusks for extra effect!) and feathers, making him a unique sight on the island. Some tribes keep a few Pegomastax around, as they are excellent scavengers who collect an extraordinary quantity of seeds and berries, while also handily gathering the rare Flowers, Mushrooms, and other ingredients necessary to cook up unusual concoctions. Tusoteuthis Vampyrus: A monstrous relative of the vampire squid, Tusoteuthis bears a closer resemblance to giant squids. It may be slow, but the aquatic Tusoteuthis is a horrific threat to anyone who dares get too close, using its tentacles to first grab, then crush...and then syphon the blood out of its hapless victims. Tribes will sometimes tame this nightmare of the deep in order to extract its unique ink, which contains oils that can be processed into fuels. Therizinosaurus Multiensis: Built like a T-Rex, but completely tameable and a herbivore to boot, the Therizinosaurus is one of the strangest dinosaurs on the islands. Its claws allow it to perform both brute-force or delicate actions; from taking down enemies (though it would prefer to just leave them alone) to plucking leaves from a particularly tasty bush. Because of this ability, Therizinosaurus are always handy to have around for harvesting specific resources, or, when needed, decimating enemies in combat. ARK: Survival Evolved is in development for Xbox One via the ID@Xbox program, Steam Early Access and PlayStation®4. The game is currently playable in on all three platforms, which includes Oculus Rift VR support and an integration of Steam community features such as Steam Economy and Steam Workshop for custom maps and mods. Players can host private/LAN servers and have access to a custom-built version of the Unreal Engine 4 Editor for creating mods. The world of ARK is designed to be modder-friendly and ever-expanding!

description: We're back with more Jalopy gameplay highlights and funny moments and although I wasn't sure it was possible, I ended up driving straight off of the map by mistake. Yes, after a flat tire and some crazy spinning out, we ended up climbing a mountain and flying off of the side into the nothingness. All that surrounds us is black and rain...BUT that's what second chances are for. Most of the parts in the car are broken down, so the question is, can we manage to limp our way back to the next city, or will we have to get home and lick our wounds prior to doing so? title: Overwatch Competitive - Bastion's Meat Shield
description: Reinhardt shields Bastion with his face while Bastion kills everyone. Overwatch is a team-based multiplayer first-person shooter video game developed and published by Blizzard Entertainment. Overwatch puts 5 kids on your team, with each child selecting either Hanzo, Widowmaker, Junkrat, Genji, or Mercy with underpowered movement, attributes, and abilities. This means you're completely BLACKED and will lose every game unless you can hypercarry. The heroes are divided into four classes: Offense, Defense, Tank and Support. This is irrelevant however because everyone just picks one of the above five characters. Players on a team work individually to secure and defend control points on a map and/or watch me fail to escort a payload across the map. Players get the same spray 13 times in a row, as they continue to lose matches. The game was launched with positive intent, while Blizzard added memes later. Additionally, Blizzard has inserted anti-meme protection but it has since been utilized by players to meme even HARDER. All Overwatch memes remain free, with the only additional cost to humanity being microtransactions to earn additional dank memes. Overwatch is Blizzard's fourth major mistake, and came about following the sinking of The Tortanic. The entire concept of Overwatch is jamming big boobs into Team Fortress 2. Basically everyone died but spirits are generally high in the optimistic near-future Earth. The developers aimed to create a diverse range of boob types and colors also a monkey. Almost no time was spent adjusting the balance of the characters, making sure that new players would throw every single game while skilled players will play the clearly op characters with instant full aoe heal. Overwatch was unveiled at BlizzCon 2014 and clamored over by morbidly obese manchildren. An open beta in May 2016 drew in more than 9.7 korean bots. The release of the game was promoted with fanservice. Upon official release, Overwatch received universal acclaim from everyone but Gaben. Overwatch has become recognized as an eSport, and in addition to sponsoring tournaments, Blizzard has announced plans to take over the world starting in 2017.

description: EXPLANATION: so bomberman is a 4 player royal rumble fight you blow up the blocks in hopes to get powerups to help trap or trick your enemy into blowing up from an explosion (caused by bombs, in case you didn't catch that) when you die in a ranked game, you go into a cart where you can drop bombs from the sidelines while you're in the cart, if your bomb is the bomb that causes the someone to die, they die but you trade into their place the reason this exploit works is that you can immediately kill yourself, and immediately run (as a cart) into your opponent's field and blow him up because he is still trapped in the corner (keep in mind: each bomberman map starts out with you being trapped in the corner, where you have to bomb yourself out. if you are being harassed at the beginning of the round, the chances of you escaping are impossible)

title: JUICY Rocket Raids (Massive RUST Loot/PvP/Heli Fights)
description: Hey, my friends. We’ve almost hit 10k YouTube subscribers! To celebrate, the artist, Tatten, hooked me up with a reworked Friduwulf logo for my YouTube and Twitch. I hope you all like the change because I absolutely love it. Tatten is also working on a new banner for both channels, so keep an eye out for that as well. The rough sketch looks amazing. Follow me on Twitter if you want to see a sneak peak of it and to stay in touch. My twitter link is in the description below. I’m thinking of starting to stream on Twitch soon, too, so follow me to stay informed when my first couple streams will be—my Twitch link is also in the description below. Enjoy the video, dudes. We do several fun rocket raids on multiple zerg groups. The following is vanilla Rust. It was a super cool few first days. We roamed and raided and got rich pretty quick, working together and fighting multiple zergs on the Reddit server. But, in all our roaming, we noticed an enormously wide compound whose privilege we could easily take over and raid tower up for their loot, so we took advantage of this opportunity to target a zerg and easily got back what we put into raiding it. In terms of Rust, building flatter wide base designs is never a good strategy when it comes to protecting your loot and retaining privilege. So, we took care of business; we raided several zergs on the reddit server, which ultimately benefited the smaller teams. Thank you very much indeed for watching this video, especially if you got this far. My next video will consist of me and two other friends defending our base from what another zerg wrongly assumed would be an offline raid. They were in for a huge surprise; I’m definitely looking forward to sharing it. See you next time, dudes. If you enjoy my content, please sub, like, share and comment on my videos. I would really appreciate it, especially as it motivates me to deliver more content. I always like to hear from you all! So, please feel welcome to share your thoughts and stories. I try to respond to each and every comment. Content Creators featured in this video: Freck's Twitch Channel:

title: Mario Kart 8: 200cc beaten with the slowest kart combination
description: i thought about a way to make the game more challenging and i decided to pick the slowest car possible going by the top speed stat. stat spread is pretty rigid so i end up with a kart with really high acceleration, which makes even blue shells seem like nothing since i get to normal speed very fast and handling is also pretty good to take corners easily. very few spots require braking to get through. in the end, it was a bit underwhelming since the CPU was pretty slow even though i set them to hard. also, this run was almost as fast as my best run in Frantic Mode which i found funny. i didn't win all tracks but the margin was so small in the ones i lost that all 1st places run wouldn't be hard at all to get (i almost got it first try without any practice) i guess i could try this with Frantic Mode items but acceleration would probably keep most hazards pretty irrelevant and might be easier than Frantic Mode with the faster karts.

title: Black Suit Spiderman Dash and Vanellope Disney Infinity 3.0 Toy Box Fun Gameplay
description: Disney Infinity 3.0 Black Suit Spiderman Dash and Vanellope Toy Box Fun Gameplay with Owen and Liam. We have some more Toy Box Fun and check out what fun things we can do with Vanellope Von Schweetz, Black Suit Spiderman, and Dash from The Incredibles Disney Infinity! Vanellope is one of the coolest Disney Infinity characters in gameplay and it should be fun to see her take on all the other Disney Infinity 3.0 gameplay characters in the Toy Box. We have some Toy Box Fun and see what kind of crazy things we can do in the Disney Infinity 3.0 Toy Box. Black Suit Spiderman from Marvel Battlegrounds is a lot of fun to play with in the Toy Box gameplay as well and his special moves are pretty awesome. We love playing with Disney Infinity Dash from Disney Infinity The Incredibles and it should be cool to see what Liam gets him up to in the Toy Box as Liam plays with Disney Infinity Black Suit Spiderman! Black Suit Spider-Man, aka Peter Parker, is the Symbiote suit version of Spider-Man. He first appeared as part of the Disney Infinity: 2.0 Edition PlayStation Vita Starter Pack. It was later confirmed that he will have a single figure release for Disney Infinity: 3.0 Edition in the Marvel Battlegrounds Play Set. When Vanellope Von Schweetz attacks another character, the character becomes temporarily glitched, just like in the movie. Vanellope's figure is missing a purple stripe on her one leg and her shoe bottoms are black instead of pink. Out of all the Disney INFNITY characters, Vanellope may have the most character interaction phrases, as she has unique phrases for several other playable characters and play set cast members when placed near them. Dashiell Robert Parr, or Dash for short, is one of the four protagonists in Disney/Pixar's 2004 hit animated feature The Incredibles. He appears as an expandable character in Disney Infinity. Dash can use his super speed to perform a rapid barrage of fast, albeit weak, punches as a melee combo, as well as travel long distances in a short time. He can also use a powerful uppercut that sends enemies up in the air, which can be followed up by either a jump kick, or a powerful kick. Here are the Disney Infinity characters we play with today: Disney Infinity Vanellope Von Schweetz Disney Infinity 3.0 Black Suit Spiderman Disney Infinity Dash Check out all of our Disney Infinity 3.0 Toy Box Fun videos!

title: Overwatch Melee with Lucio, Mercy, Mei,  Bastion and D.va
description: Punch Break! Overwatch gameplay of people getting punched in the face. Melee is best DPS. Featuring: Lucio, Mercy, Mei, Bastion and D.va Overwatch is a team-based multiplayer first-person shooter video game developed and published by Blizzard Entertainment. Overwatch puts 5 kids on your team, with each child selecting either Hanzo, Widowmaker, Junkrat, Genji, or Mercy with underpowered movement, attributes, and abilities. This means you're completely BLACKED and will lose every game unless you can hypercarry. The heroes are divided into four classes: Offense, Defense, Tank and Support. This is irrelevant however because everyone just picks one of the above five characters. Players on a team work individually to secure and defend control points on a map and/or watch me fail to escort a payload across the map. Players get the same spray 13 times in a row, as they continue to lose matches. The game was launched with positive intent, while Blizzard added memes later. Additionally, Blizzard has inserted anti-meme protection but it has since been utilized by players to meme even HARDER. All Overwatch memes remain free, with the only additional cost to humanity being microtransactions to earn additional dank memes. Overwatch is Blizzard's fourth major mistake, and came about following the sinking of The Tortanic. The entire concept of Overwatch is jamming big boobs into Team Fortress 2. Basically everyone died but spirits are generally high in the optimistic near-future Earth. The developers aimed to create a diverse range of boob types and colors also a monkey. Almost no time was spent adjusting the balance of the characters, making sure that new players would throw every single game while skilled players will play the clearly op characters with instant full aoe heal. Overwatch was unveiled at BlizzCon 2014 and clamored over by morbidly obese manchildren. An open beta in May 2016 drew in more than 9.7 korean bots. The release of the game was promoted with fanservice. Upon official release, Overwatch received universal acclaim from everyone but Gaben. Overwatch has become recognized as an eSport, and in addition to sponsoring tournaments, Blizzard has announced plans to take over the world starting in 2017.

title: Response to Markiplier | I Feel Lost
description: I've decided to respond to Markiplier's recent video entitled, "I Feel Lost." Only reason is because I don't necessarily believe anyone should feel lost, even in what they do. I can relate to the emotion of feeling lost as I've felt the same way myself more then once. So I thought it would be necessary to respond to Markiplier himself for once. Will he actually see this video? Probably not. But at least my subscribers can get something out of it... maybe. ---------- I am DarkWolf, and I do Let's Plays. I've been a gamer since I was young, playing with my NES and my Game Boy. Over the years I started to swing towards the PC gaming scene. Now I do obscure PC games and indie titles. As I have gotten tired of the rinse, wash, and repeat mentality of the mainstream titles, I have been focusing on the releases of the underdogs, shining a spotlight on these hidden gems and giving exposure and commentary to the up-and-coming talent in game development. title: GDC 2017 Flash Forward:  Motion Warping in Gears of War 4: Doing More with Less
description: The sheer magnitude of animation assets needed to build smooth and realistic movement systems while keeping a character grounded in an uneven and dynamic environment has changed how animation behaviors are built and authored. Blending multiple animations has traditionally been a way of dealing with distance, direction and environmental variance. However, the amount of assets needed for adequate coverage in today's large AAA titles can be crushing. Multiple animation blending also reduces visual freedom as blended animations must be of similar style and timing. Some games have tackled this content explosion by dynamically warping motion to meet the spatial constraints. These are often ad hoc/specific to particular actions and not exposed to the animator. For 'Gears of War 4', The Coalition developed a generalized solution by introducing the concept of warp points. Steven Dickinson | Technical Animator at The Coalition, Microsoft Location: Room 132, North Hall Date: Wednesday, March 1 Time: 11:00am - 11:30am Format: Session Track: Visual Arts Pass Type: GDC All Access, GDC All Access + VRDC, GDC Main Conference, GDC Main Conference + VRDC - Get your pass now! title: World of Warships - Why Pick French Cruisers?
description: So my Twitch stream brought up a good point, Why pick a french cruiser over a soviet destroyer. I thought about it and just had no answer, because I knew the Soviet Destroyers perform all the goals of the French Cruiser much better. Speed, Firepower, Tankability through avoiding damage, and better torpedoes. The only thing they give up is the ability to use defensive fire and speed boost, but clearly they're fast enough as is without the skill. I think the bigger issue is that Cruisers in general are easily replaced with higher damage, tank, or supportive cruisers who bring a bunch of consumables. I'm inclined to encourage more utility in cruisers to get more play out of them but what do you think? Hope this was interesting and have a wonderful day! title: Brick Rigs Game | VEHICLE CARRIER VS THE TRAIN! | Lets Play Brick Rigs Gameplay & Highlights
description: And welcome back once again to some more Brick Rigs gameplay! In this episode we try out some more user creations from the steam workshop and then try and stop the train once again! It's the Vehicle Carrier vs The Train! --- In this episode of Brick Rigs we look at a few more user creations from the steam workshop! ALL of them have been so amazing! The Rock Crawler can climb rocks, the bomb transporter can transport bombs, its like everything is just working! So in this Brick Rigs update, they added planes, machine guns and huge explosive rounds!! GUYS! The destruction and explosions that we can make are ENDLESS!! In this Brick Rigs video, I will be showing off the air planes, but most importantly, massive explosions! Today we will be doing something I vowed to do a few episodes ago, and that is DESTROYING THE ENTIRE CITY!!! MUAHAHAH!! OKAY SO THE HOMIES OVER AT BRICK RIDGE STUDIOS (thats not what its called lol) released yet ANOTHER UPDATE!! So this update introduces Multiplayer! Multiplayer is exactly what Brick Ridge needs, except its a bit buggy right now. It seems that with every update and patch released, something else breaks. The Multiplayer is hard because it crashes the game a LOT. Connectivity is also a big issue as well. Another issue with the multiplayer currently is the inability to spawn in user created workshop builds, so we are stuck with what currently came with the game. That being said, Multiplayer is an amazing update! I cannot wait for the multiplayer to work and to get some collabs going with some other youtubers! Keep in mind, this patch also seemed to have broke some things.. like.. tires spinning properly. If driving was hard before, its almost impossible in this new update on the race track, lol. So today in Brick Rigs, we are going to look at the FASTEST CAR EVER BUILT EVER! And a super fast camper as well! Guys! Yall are making some AMAZING creations! This car is so friken fast, its uncontrollable, but makes for some amazing jumps! I love going fast and this car is perfect for me! GUYS!! BRICK RIGS HAD AN UPDATE!! Okay so the first update for Brick Rigs introduces less game crashes (yeah right lol) and an amazing addition of the workshop! The steam workshop is such a great feature and a game such as brick rigs absolutely needs it! It is so fantastic to see the developers of Brick Rigs updating the game and pushing out patches so soon! That's a great sign! Today in Brick Rigs, we are going to look at the Attack Helicopter, Dirt Bike and more!! The Attack Helicopter, like any Chopper / Helicopter, is SUPER DIFFICULT to control!! But, I'm gonna try of course! The Dirt Bike seems to have a mind of its own, spazzing out uncontrollably at every turn rofl. Anyways guys I hope y'all enjoy the Dirt Bike and Attack Helicopter! Brick Rigs Gameplay Anyways, today in Brick Rigs we try out the Steam Workshop introduced in the new patch. I downloaded 3 user creations! We have the Semi Truck aka Freight truck, a tank and also a fast car. I don't know if the fast car is the fastest car, but I gotta assume, that it is. The tank is also amazing to drive because it actually works! You can shoot, rotate the gun thing and all! Brick Rigs Gameplay The semi truck had to be my favorite however because I work with freight trucks all day! It was so fun driving the freight truck, the tank, and the fastest car! Brick Rigs Gameplay Welcome to Brick Rigs Gameplay! Today, we try out a new lego simulator called Brick Rigs. Brick Rigs, still in VERY EARLY ACCESS, tries to be a Lego Simulator. I read some reviews on Brick Rigs, and apparently others have found it easy to build.. I on the other hand, had a horrendous time figuring this game out. Brick Rigs is a game that shows a ton of potential, but needs time to get polished, IMO. What to Expect in this Brick Rigs Gameplay Video: Brick Rigs Gameplay Brick Rigs Lets Play Brick Rigs Highlights Brick Rigs Building Brick Rigs Review Brick Rigs allows you to build many kinds of vehicles from a variety of bricks and experience their dynamic driving and destruction physics in a sandbox environment. Brick Rigs online multiplayer Brick Rigs patch Brick Rigs update Brick Rigs third update Brick Rigs online Brick Rigs multiplayer This is an early version of the game, and I would like to get as much feedback from the community as possible about the gameplay, physics and what direction the game should head. Will our Pokemon survive the home stretch? RULES OF THE WONDERLOCKE: 1. Any Pokemon that faints is considered dead, and it may not be used anymore throughout the course of gameplay. 2. You may only catch the first Pokemon encountered in each area. 3. As soon as it is available, every Pokemon caught must be Wonder Traded at the soonest opportunity, and the new Pokemon you receive is what you may use. 4. Any shiny Pokemon encountered are exempt from Rules 2 and 3. They may be caught and used at any point, and they do not have to be Wonder Traded. However if they faint, they will still be considered dead.
